import re

def parse_email(email):
    email_regex = ''
    result = re.search(email_regex, email)
    if result:
        valid = True
        (username, domain) = email.split('@')
        elements = domain.split('.')
        tld = elements[-1]
        subdomains = elements[0:-1]
        subdomains = '.'.join(subdomains)
    else:
        valid = False
        username = domain = tld = subdomains = None
    return {'valid': valid, 'username': username, 'domain': domain, 'tld': tld, 'subdomains': subdomains}
